## `<file-level: imports and EntryRow>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-1 -->

### Purpose
CRUD over the `entries` table. A directory entry is `(parent, name, inode)`. Multiple entries with the same `inode` = hard links. Plan.v3 split these from `nodes`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use rusqlite::{Connection, OptionalExtension, params};

use crate::errors::{Error, Result};
use crate::types::NodeKind;
use crate::nodes;  // for kind-filtered count join

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub struct EntryRow {
    pub parent: u64,
    pub name:   String,
    pub inode:  u64,
}
```

---

## `pub fn insert(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, name: &str, inode: u64) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-2 -->

### Preconditions
- `parent` is an existing dir-kind inode (caller enforces).
- `name` is a validated path component.
- `inode` exists in `nodes`.
- No row with `(parent, name)` already exists.

### Failure Modes
- `UNIQUE(parent, name)` violation: returns `Error::AlreadyExists(...)`. Map by inspecting the sqlite error kind — constraint violation → `AlreadyExists`; re-wrap anything else via `#[from]`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn insert(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, name: &str, inode: u64) -> Result<()> {
    let res = conn.execute(
        "INSERT INTO entries (parent, name, inode) VALUES (?1, ?2, ?3)",
        params![parent as i64, name, inode as i64],
    );
    match res {
        Ok(_) => Ok(()),
        Err(rusqlite::Error::SqliteFailure(e, _))
            if e.code == rusqlite::ErrorCode::ConstraintViolation =>
        {
            Err(Error::AlreadyExists(format!(
                "entry {name:?} already exists under inode {parent}"
            )))
        }
        Err(e) => Err(Error::Sqlite(e)),
    }
}
```

---

## `pub fn get(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, name: &str) -> Result<EntryRow>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-3 -->

### Failure Modes
- No such entry: `Err(Error::NotFound(...))`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn get(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, name: &str) -> Result<EntryRow> {
    let row = conn.query_row(
        "SELECT parent, name, inode FROM entries WHERE parent = ?1 AND name = ?2",
        params![parent as i64, name],
        |r| Ok(EntryRow {
            parent: r.get::<_, i64>(0)? as u64,
            name:   r.get(1)?,
            inode:  r.get::<_, i64>(2)? as u64,
        }),
    ).optional()?;
    row.ok_or_else(|| Error::NotFound(format!("no entry {name:?} under inode {parent}")))
}
```

---

## `pub fn delete(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, name: &str) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-4 -->

### Postconditions
- Row `(parent, name)` removed. If absent, no-op (caller has checked existence).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn delete(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, name: &str) -> Result<()> {
    conn.execute(
        "DELETE FROM entries WHERE parent = ?1 AND name = ?2",
        params![parent as i64, name],
    )?;
    Ok(())
}
```

