## `pub fn list(conn: &Connection, parent: u64) -> Result<Vec<EntryRow>>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-5 -->

### Purpose
List all entries under a directory inode. Ordered by `name ASC` for stability.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn list(conn: &Connection, parent: u64) -> Result<Vec<EntryRow>> {
    let mut stmt = conn.prepare(
        "SELECT parent, name, inode FROM entries WHERE parent = ?1 ORDER BY name ASC",
    )?;
    let rows = stmt.query_map(params![parent as i64], |r| Ok(EntryRow {
        parent: r.get::<_, i64>(0)? as u64,
        name:   r.get(1)?,
        inode:  r.get::<_, i64>(2)? as u64,
    }))?;
    let mut out = Vec::new();
    for row in rows { out.push(row?); }
    Ok(out)
}
```

---

## `pub fn count(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, kind: Option<NodeKind>) -> Result<u64>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-6 -->

### Purpose
Count entries under `parent`, optionally filtered by the child node's kind. Used for `rmdir` non-empty check and directory `nlink` math.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn count(conn: &Connection, parent: u64, kind: Option<NodeKind>) -> Result<u64> {
    let n: i64 = match kind {
        None => conn.query_row(
            "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM entries WHERE parent = ?1",
            params![parent as i64],
            |r| r.get(0),
        )?,
        Some(k) => {
            let ks = match k {
                NodeKind::File => "file",
                NodeKind::Dir => "dir",
                NodeKind::Symlink => "symlink",
            };
            conn.query_row(
                "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM entries e
                 JOIN nodes n ON n.inode = e.inode
                 WHERE e.parent = ?1 AND n.kind = ?2",
                params![parent as i64, ks],
                |r| r.get(0),
            )?
        }
    };
    Ok(n as u64)
}
```

---

## `pub fn rename(conn, old_parent, old_name, new_parent, new_name) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-7 -->

### Purpose
Move an existing entry. `(old_parent, old_name)` becomes `(new_parent, new_name)`; the pointed-at `inode` is preserved.

### Preconditions
- `(old_parent, old_name)` exists.
- `(new_parent, new_name)` does not exist (caller responsible).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn rename(
    conn: &Connection,
    old_parent: u64, old_name: &str,
    new_parent: u64, new_name: &str,
) -> Result<()> {
    let res = conn.execute(
        "UPDATE entries SET parent = ?1, name = ?2 WHERE parent = ?3 AND name = ?4",
        params![new_parent as i64, new_name, old_parent as i64, old_name],
    );
    match res {
        Ok(_) => Ok(()),
        Err(rusqlite::Error::SqliteFailure(e, _))
            if e.code == rusqlite::ErrorCode::ConstraintViolation =>
        {
            Err(Error::AlreadyExists(format!(
                "entry {new_name:?} already exists under inode {new_parent}"
            )))
        }
        Err(e) => Err(Error::Sqlite(e)),
    }
}
```

---

## `pub fn parent_of(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<Option<u64>>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-8 -->

### Purpose
Return the parent of a dir-kind inode. Directories have exactly one entry (v1 forbids hard links to dirs). Root returns `None`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn parent_of(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<Option<u64>> {
    let row: Option<i64> = conn.query_row(
        "SELECT parent FROM entries WHERE inode = ?1 LIMIT 1",
        params![inode as i64],
        |r| r.get(0),
    ).optional()?;
    Ok(row.map(|v| v as u64))
}
```

---

## `pub fn ancestry(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<Vec<u64>>`
<!-- checksum: rust-entries-9 -->

### Purpose
Walk ancestors from `inode` up to root via `entries`. Used by `fs.rs` rename-into-own-subtree check and fsck cycle detection. Empty vec if `inode` is root.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn ancestry(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<Vec<u64>> {
    let mut out = Vec::new();
    let mut cur = inode;
    loop {
        match parent_of(conn, cur)? {
            Some(p) => { out.push(p); cur = p; }
            None    => break,
        }
    }
    Ok(out)
}
```

